      • BREACH_IF_NO_TRADING_PRICE_ATTR

        public static final String BREACH_IF_NO_TRADING_PRICE_ATTR
        Breach if no trading price attribute name. Order value and exposure will not be updated if there is no trading price. TODO Investigate to move this attribute to compliance filter set. Currently there can be multiple filters associated with one filter state controller. If this changes and we need this attribute inside filter state controller.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DEFAULT_BREAKOUT_BOX_ANNOTATION_TAG

        public static final int DEFAULT_BREAKOUT_BOX_ANNOTATION_TAG
        The default tag added to broken out messages. This default value means that broken out messages are not annotated by default. The BREAKOUT_BOX_ANNOTATION_TAG_ATTR must be set to a positive value for annotation to occur.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • makeFromFixFilterContext

        protected FromFixFilterContext makeFromFixFilterContext(IFIXMessage message)
                                                 throws Exception
        Create a basic skeleton context for the use by filters.

        The context created here only contains static information from the message itself. No calculations which require market data information are performed. Filters which require a more complete context must fill in the missing context as required.

        Parameters:
        message - The message from FIX.
        Returns:
        The from FIX filter context. This context is incomplete. Filters requiring a complete context must fill in the missing context as required.
        Throws:
        Exception - TBD

      • doProcessFilterBreachException

        protected boolean doProcessFilterBreachException(FilterBreachException e,
                                                 IFIXMessage msg)
                                          throws Exception
        Allow subclasses to override the default filter breach exception processing.
        Parameters:
        e - The filter breach exception.
        msg - The message causing the breach.
        Returns:
        True if the filter breach exception was processed implying that no further processing is required, false if the exception was not processed implying that the default processing should take place.
        Throws:
        Exception - On filter breach exception processing failure.
